text: Conotrochus is a genus of small corals in the family Caryophylliidae. It holds four species. ==Species== The World Register of Marine Species includes the following species in the genus: *Conotrochus asymmetros Cairns, 1999 *Conotrochus brunneus (Moseley, 1881) *Conotrochus funicolumna (Alcock, 1902) *Conotrochus typus † Seguenza, 1863 ==References== Category:Caryophylliidae Category:Scleractinia genera
title: Conotrochus
